draw((0,-8)--(0,8),Arrows(6));

label("$x$", (8,0), E);
label("$y$", (0,8), N);

draw(graph(funcg,-3,3),red);
[/asy]

Then, we can shift the graph four units to the right.  Thus,
\[g(x) = f(-(x - 4)) = \boxed{f(4 - x)}.\]

question:
How many degrees are in the sum of the measures of the six numbered angles pictured? [asy]
draw((3,8)--(10,4)--(1,0)--cycle,linewidth(1));
